HEADWORD: Fulgurata
<hw>Ful"gu*ra"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Electricity)</fld> <def>A spectro-electric tube in which the
decomposition of a liquid by the passage of an electric spark is
observed.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

